step.reason:
\text{Only matrices having the {\bf same order} i.e.}\\
\text{equal no. of rows (m) and equal no. of}\\
\text{columns (n) can be subtracted.}

A_{m \times n} - B_{m \times n} = D_{m \times n}\\
\text{Thus, resultant matrix D has m rows and}\\
\text{n columns.}

A_{m \times n} - B_{m \times n} = D_{m \times n} = [d_{ij}]_{m \times n}\\
\text{where } d_{ij} = a_{ij} - b_{ij} \, (\forall \text{ possible ij values}).\\
\text{Thus, corresponding elements are subtracted.}
